              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">Wall Street slips after recent rally</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.longandshort.com/email/images/ls-jan-17-1.png" alt="Wall Street slips after recent rally" href="https://www.altdaily.co" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Wall Street cooled off after Wednesday’s big rally, with <a href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-17-01-2025-h1-1-major-indexes-slipping" target="_blank">major indexes slipping</a>. Investors weighed corporate earnings and economic data for signs of Federal Reserve rate cut plans. Morgan Stanley surged on strong Q4 profits, while UnitedHealth dropped due to missed sales estimates. Treasury yields fell as Fed Governor Waller hinted at quicker rate cuts. The Dow fell 0.16%, the S&P 500 lost 0.21%, and the Nasdaq dropped 0.89%. Apple saw a 4% decline after being overtaken in China’s smartphone market.</p>
        </mj-text>
