              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">Target's guidance lift fails to reassure</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4; filter: blur(5px)">Target raised its sales guidance after a strong holiday season, but it wasn’t enough to address Wall Street’s <a href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-17-01-2025-h2-2-profitability-concerns" target="_blank">profitability concerns</a>. Shares fell nearly 5% as analysts noted that discounting likely hurt margins. Despite improved discretionary product sales like apparel and toys, competition from Amazon and Walmart remains a challenge. Target’s leadership shuffle aims to drive growth. With mixed results across retail, the company faces hurdles in regaining investor confidence.</p>
        </mj-text>
